    b"enough for the request without thinking about it too much.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Search sur"
    b"faces:\x0d\x0a        - tags: exact memory tags. They are not substring searched.\x0d\x0a   "
    b"     - strings.contains: case-insensitive text fragments. Each value is checked\x0d"
    b"\x0a          as a substring against searchable memory content.\x0d\x0a        - strings."
    b"equals: exact text values. Each value is checked for exact\x0d\x0a          equality a"
    b"gainst searchable memory content.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Optional outputs available in this "
    b"step:\x0d\x0a        - candidate_memory: a vague remembered observation that could be "
    b"useful to\x0d\x0a          preserve.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Rules:\x0d\x0a        - Return only search h"
    b"ints and optional candidate_memory.\x0d\x0a        - Search hints are alternatives dur"
    b"ing retrieval; a memory can be useful\x0d\x0a          when any positive tag or string"
    b" hint matches.\x0d\x0a        - Prefer tags.any_of for positive tag hints.\x0d\x0a        - "
    b"Leave tags.all_of empty unless compatibility with older memories needs it.\x0d\x0a    "
    b"    - Use tags.none_of only for clear exclusions.\x0d\x0a        - Use strings.contain"
    b"s for durable words or phrases that should appear\x0d\x0a          inside a relevant m"
    b"emory.\x0d\x0a        - Use strings.equals only for exact text that should match a rel"
    b"evant\x0d\x0a          memory value as a whole.\x0d\x0a        - Prefer a small set of high-"
    b"signal hints over broad keyword stuffing.\x0d\x0a        - Return empty arrays when no"
    b" useful search hint is available.\x0d\x0a        - Use optional outputs only when they"
